    ref:'Ecclesiastes 9:10',
    imgQuery:'Camiguin White Island sandbar Philippines',
    reflection:'There\'s a temptation to save your best effort for the tasks that matter — the client-facing project, the presentation the boss will see — while coasting through the routine, low-visibility work that seems to count for nothing. But Ecclesiastes doesn\'t qualify its instruction with \'when it matters\' or \'when someone\'s watching.\' It says whatever your hand finds, meaning the mundane data entry and the important pitch get the same standard. This isn\'t about burning yourself out on trivial tasks; it\'s about refusing to let visibility determine your effort level. A person who is only excellent when it counts hasn\'t actually built excellence — they\'ve built performance.',
