    title:'Retrenched and Still Whole',
    verse:'The Lord is close to the brokenhearted and saves those who are crushed in spirit.',
    ref:'Psalm 34:18',
    imgQuery:'Subic Bay Freeport coast Zambales Philippines',
    reflection:'The layoff notice came without much warning, and along with the practical scramble to find something next, there\'s a deeper crushing that\'s harder to name — the feeling that you failed somehow, that your usefulness has an expiration date the company just enforced. Being let go, even for reasons that have nothing to do with your performance, can crush your sense of self in ways a mere inconvenience wouldn\'t. Psalm 34 doesn\'t promise the layoff won\'t hurt. It promises God\'s specific nearness to exactly this kind of crushing — not distant sympathy, but closeness in the actual brokenness. Your value was never actually tied to your employment status, even though right now it might feel like it was.',
    takeaways:['A layoff can crush identity even when it\'s not a reflection of your performance.','God promises specific closeness to the brokenhearted, not distant sympathy.','Your value was never actually tied to your employment status.'],
