    reflection:'Paul, arguably history\'s most influential missionary, spent long stretches earning his living through ordinary manual labor, sewing tents alongside Aquila and Priscilla in a city that wasn\'t his home. His calling to preach the gospel didn\'t exempt him from the practical, unglamorous work of earning a wage far from familiar ground. If Paul\'s ministry could coexist with tentmaking, your career abroad — however far from your sense of higher purpose it feels — can coexist with a genuine calling too. You don\'t need to abandon your job to matter to God\'s kingdom. Like Paul, you might be exactly positioned, tent-stitching and all, for purposes bigger than the paycheck suggests.',
