    title:'The Notification You Don\'t Have to Answer at Midnight',
    verse:'It is he who gives strength to the weary and increases the power of the weak.',
    ref:'Isaiah 40:29',
    imgQuery:'Palawan Coron mountain lake Kayangan Philippines',
    reflection:'The phone buzzes at midnight with a work message, and your thumb is already reaching for it before you\'ve even considered whether it can wait until morning. Constant availability has quietly become the expectation, unspoken but real, and you\'ve internalized it as part of being a good employee. Isaiah\'s promise of strength for the weary assumes there is a state of being weary that needs replenishing — which means depletion isn\'t meant to be your permanent condition. Refusing to answer every midnight notification isn\'t neglecting your job; it\'s protecting the very strength that job depends on you having tomorrow. Even God, who never sleeps, gave His people a rhythm that included rest.',
