    ref:'Proverbs 17:17',
    imgQuery:'Zambales Anawangin sunset pine cove Philippines',
    reflection:'There\'s a lunch group you\'re never invited to, a project thread you\'re quietly left off of, a joke in the chat you didn\'t catch the reference to because you weren\'t included in the conversation that spawned it. Workplace exclusion, even when subtle and probably unintentional, still stings in a very human way. Proverbs\' picture of friendship — loving at all times, showing up specifically in adversity — is a reminder that not every relationship you need has to come from the group that\'s currently excluding you. God often provides a smaller, truer circle instead of a broader popular one. Look for the friend actually built for hard seasons rather than chasing entry into a clique that hasn\'t chosen you.',
