    title:'The Birthday You Celebrated Through a Screen',
    verse:'Weep with those who weep.',
    ref:'Romans 12:15',
    imgQuery:'Biliran hot springs waterfalls Eastern Visayas Philippines',
    reflection:'You sang happy birthday over a shaky video call, watched a cake get cut through a pixelated screen, and then closed the laptop and went straight back to an ordinary workday like nothing significant had just happened. There\'s a particular grief in celebrating milestones remotely and then immediately having to function normally, with no space to actually process what that cost you emotionally. Romans 12:15 calls believers to weep with those who weep — and that includes weeping with your own grief, not just other people\'s. You\'re allowed to acknowledge that the screen-birthday hurt, even while being grateful you got to see it at all. Both things can be true at once.',
