    ref:'Ecclesiastes 4:6',
    imgQuery:'Camarines Norte Calaguas Island Philippines',
    reflection:'Extra shifts mean extra pay, and in your situation extra pay always seems justified — another debt to pay down, another relative\'s need, another goal that feels urgent. So you keep saying yes, even as your body and your relationships quietly pay the price for the overtime your wallet collects. Ecclesiastes\' blunt comparison isn\'t anti-work; it\'s anti-toil-without-limit, the kind of chasing that never actually arrives anywhere satisfying no matter how many extra handfuls you gather. One handful held with tranquility outweighs two grabbed at the cost of your peace. Not every extra shift needs to be taken just because it\'s offered. Some of them are worth declining for the sake of what overtime can\'t buy back.',
