    reflection:'You had it mapped out — this job by this year, this savings goal by this date, this milestone before turning a certain age — and none of it happened the way the spreadsheet said it would. There\'s a specific grief in watching a carefully built plan dissolve, not through your negligence but through circumstances entirely outside your control. Jeremiah\'s promise wasn\'t given to people whose plans worked out; it was given to exiles whose entire national plan had just collapsed. God\'s declared plans for prosperity and hope didn\'t depend on their five-year plan succeeding — His plans operated on a different, longer timeline altogether. Your fallen-apart spreadsheet isn\'t evidence God\'s plan failed too.',
