    title:'Praying for the Boss You Can\'t Stand',
    verse:'But I tell you, love your enemies and pray for those who persecute you.',
    ref:'Matthew 5:44',
    imgQuery:'Tawi-Tawi Sibutu Island coral reef Philippines',
    reflection:'Your boss isn\'t technically your enemy, but some days the frustration feels close enough — the unreasonable demands, the credit-taking, the way criticism lands harder than any acknowledgment ever does. Jesus\'s command to love and pray for those who persecute you wasn\'t written for comfortable relationships; it was written specifically for the hard ones, the people who genuinely make your life difficult. Praying for a difficult boss doesn\'t mean pretending their behavior is fine or asking God to bless their unfairness. It means refusing to let your heart calcify into pure resentment, choosing instead to hand that relationship to God directly, trusting He can work in someone\'s character even when you can\'t.',
