    verse:'Be still, and know that I am God.',
    ref:'Psalm 46:10',
    imgQuery:'Capiz Suhot Cave river Panay Philippines',
    reflection:'Sunday used to mean church, rest, a genuine break, but lately even your day off is spent catching up on chores, replying to messages, mentally rehearsing Monday\'s demands. Stillness has started to feel unproductive, almost uncomfortable, like your mind doesn\'t know how to stop moving even when your body finally has the chance to. Psalm 46:10 is a command, not a suggestion — be still — issued to people in the middle of real chaos, nations in uproar, mountains falling into the sea. If stillness was possible then, it\'s possible now, even for someone whose nervous system has forgotten what it feels like. Knowing God requires actually stopping long enough to notice He\'s still there.',
