    imgQuery:'Quezon Province Kwebang Lampas cave Philippines',
    reflection:'Your parents sacrificed to send you to school for a specific career, and now that you\'re actually in it, you\'ve realized it isn\'t who you are — but disappointing them after everything they gave up feels almost unthinkable. Ephesians gives instruction in both directions, honoring parents genuinely while also acknowledging that parents shouldn\'t exasperate their children into resentment through unreasonable demands. Honoring your parents doesn\'t require permanently silencing your own convictions about your calling. It means approaching a potential shift honestly, respectfully, and with genuine gratitude for what they sacrificed, rather than either blind obedience or a rebellious break. Both honor and honesty can coexist in that hard conversation.',
