    reflection:'You said yes to the extra shift again, telling yourself it\'s temporary, it\'s for the family, it\'s just this month. But months stack into years, and your body has been quietly keeping score of every shortened night. David wrote this verse while literally being pursued by enemies, and still he could say his sleep came from a peace rooted in God\'s safety, not in his circumstances being resolved. Your safety net isn\'t ultimately the overtime pay — it\'s God\'s provision, which frees you to actually protect your sleep instead of sacrificing it indefinitely in the name of security that sleep deprivation itself starts to undermine.',
