    verse:'Do you not know that your bodies are temples of the Holy Spirit?',
    ref:'1 Corinthians 6:19',
    imgQuery:'Twin Falls forest Bukidnon Philippines',
    reflection:'It\'s easy to treat your body as purely instrumental abroad — a machine that clocks in, lifts, stands, or sits for hours, and should simply keep functioning regardless of how it\'s treated. Paul\'s description flips that entirely: your body isn\'t just a tool for output, it\'s a temple, a place where God\'s Spirit actually dwells. That reframes basic self-care — eating real meals, getting sunlight, seeing a doctor when something\'s wrong, sleeping enough — from indulgence into stewardship. Neglecting your body isn\'t a neutral choice with no spiritual weight; it\'s neglecting the very dwelling place you\'ve been given to steward.',
