    title:'Paid Less, Valued No Less by God',
    verse:'The stone the builders rejected has become the cornerstone.',
    ref:'Psalm 118:22',
    imgQuery:'Biliran hot springs waterfalls Philippines',
    reflection:'Wage gaps between foreign and local workers doing comparable work are a documented reality in many industries, and living inside that gap can quietly teach you to internalize a lower sense of your own value, as if the pay scale is an accurate measure of your worth. This psalm describes rejection followed by exaltation — a stone dismissed by the very people responsible for evaluating it, later becoming the load-bearing cornerstone. That pattern shows up again in how Jesus Himself was treated. Being undervalued by a system doesn\'t determine your actual value. Sometimes the most rejected stone turns out to be the one everything else depends on.',
